---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Community" description="Community life on The Ridge, regular dog walks, people walks and bike rides, and the everyday good-neighbour habits that keep our trails and parkland welcoming.">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Community life</p>
      <h1>How neighbours connect on the Ridge</h1>
      <p class="lead prose">
        The Ridge is more than a collection of houses – it’s a place to build ongoing connections. This space is for neighbours to start and grow small groups that meet regularly, whether that’s walking, riding, sharing hobbies, or just catching up. As more groups form, we create more chances to see each other week after week, on the trails, in the parkland, and along our quiet streets. Everyone’s welcome to join in or to start something new that fits your interests and pace.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The view we share -->
  <section class="section" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="container">
      <figure class="photo-wide">
        <img src="/img/ridge-mountains.jpg" width="1800" height="1350" alt="Snow-capped Coast Mountains and autumn colour beyond the forest, seen from the Ridge." loading="lazy" />
        <figcaption>Autumn light over the mountains, from the edge of the neighbourhood.</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- A neighbourhood in bloom -->
  <section class="section" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="container">
      <figure class="photo-feature">
        <img src="/img/ridge-garden.jpg" width="1200" height="1600" alt="A deep-red dahlia in bloom in a Ridge front-garden bed." loading="lazy" />
        <figcaption>Front-garden colour on the Ridge in high summer.</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" style="padding-top:0;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="panel-forest neighbours">
        <h2 style="margin-top:0;">Good neighbours on the trails</h2>
        <p>
          Our trails, park and fields are shared by everyone, kids, dogs, walkers,
          riders, and the wildlife that was here first. A few gentle habits keep them
          a joy for all of us.
        </p>
        <div class="grid cols-3">
          <div class="note">
            <h3>Mind the dogs</h3>
            <p>Leash up around little ones and other dogs, and always pick up after your pup, carry a spare bag or two for a neighbour who's run out.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="note">
            <h3>Share the path</h3>
            <p>A friendly hello goes a long way. Riders, slow down and call out when passing; walkers, keep an ear open and make a little room.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="note">
            <h3>Respect the parkland</h3>
            <p>Keep to the paths where you can, take your litter home, and give the fields and plantings time to grow. Leave each spot as lovely as you found it.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p style="margin-bottom:0;">
          Thanks for looking out for each other, it's what makes this place feel like home.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .photo-wide { margin: 0; }
  .photo-wide img {
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow);
    display: block;
  }
  .photo-wide figcaption {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: var(--fs-sm);
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
  }
  .photo-feature { margin: var(--space-4) auto 0; max-width: 460px; }
  .photo-feature img {
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 4 / 5;
    object-fit: cover;
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
    display: block;
  }
  .photo-feature figcaption {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: var(--fs-sm);
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-top: var(--space-1);
  }
  .neighbours .note h3 { color: #fff; margin-bottom: var(--space-1); }
  .neighbours .grid { margin: var(--space-3) 0; }
</style>
